#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:1
msgid "Runtime settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:3
msgid "Selecting between multiple object factories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:5
msgid ""
"The `vtkObjectFactory` mechanism supports registering multiple "
"implementations of a class at runtime. By default, VTK uses the first "
"registered implementation, which can cause conflicts if different modules "
"register different implementations of the same class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:7
msgid ""
"To control which implementation is selected, provide a preferences string to "
"`vtkObjectFactory`. The string lists attribute keys with a list of values "
"ordered by priority, using the format `key=value1,value2`, and separates "
"attributes with semicolons (e.g., `keyA=valueA1,valueA2;keyB=valueB1,"
"valueB2`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:9
msgid ""
"In the below examples, the vtkObjectFactory prefers implementations that "
"have `valueA1` over `valueA2` for an attribute `keyA`, and if that fails, "
"`valueB1` over `valueB2` for an attribute `keyB`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:11
msgid "The three possible ways to set the preferences are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:12
msgid ""
"Set the environment variable `VTK_FACTORY_PREFER` before starting your "
"application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:13
msgid "VTK_FACTORY_PREFER=\"keyA=valueA1,valueA2;keyB=valueB1,valueB2\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:16
msgid ""
"Call the static method `vtkObjectFactory::SetPreferences()` before creating "
"any VTK objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:18
msgid ""
"vtkObjectFactory::SetPreferences(\"keyA=valueA1,valueA2;keyB=valueB1,"
"valueB2\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:21
msgid ""
"Call the static method `vtkObjectFactory::"
"InitializePreferencesFromCommandLineArgs(argc, argv)` early in your "
"application, passing the command line arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:23
msgid ""
"int main(int argc, char* argv[])\n"
"{\n"
"  vtkObjectFactory::InitializePreferencesFromCommandLineArgs(argc, argv);\n"
"  // ...\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:31
msgid ""
"# Example preference string ('=' sign can be omitted and replaced with a "
"space)\n"
"./my_vtk_app --vtk-factory-prefer=\"keyA=valueA1,valueA2;keyB=valueB1,"
"valueB2\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:36
msgid "Override Attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:38
msgid ""
"Here is a list of attributes that are recognized in the VTK factory "
"preferences string. These attributes are used as keys in the "
"`VTK_FACTORY_PREFER` environment variable (or equivalently via "
"`vtkObjectFactory::SetPreferences()` or the `--vtk-factory-prefer` command-"
"line option) using the format described above (for example: `Platform=macOS;"
"RenderingBackend=OpenGL`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "Attribute Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "Possible Values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "Platform"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "`Embedded`,`iOS`,`macOS`,`WebAssembly`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "RenderingBackend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "`OpenGL`, `WebGPU`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "WindowSystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:0
msgid "`Cocoa`,`EGL`,`HTML5`,`OffScreenMESA`,`X11`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:46
msgid "OpenGL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:48
msgid ""
"On Linux and Windows, VTK will attempt to detect support for an OpenGL "
"context backend at runtime and create an appropriate subclass of "
"`vtkOpenGLRenderWindow`. You can override this process by specifying an "
"environment variable `VTK_DEFAULT_OPENGL_WINDOW`. The possible values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:53
msgid ""
"`vtkXOpenGLRenderWindow` (Linux; applicable only when `VTK_USE_X` is `ON`, "
"which is the default setting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:54
msgid ""
"`vtkWin32OpenGLRenderWindow` (Windows; applicable only when "
"`VTK_USE_WIN32_OPENGL` is `ON`, which is the default setting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:55
msgid ""
"`vtkEGLRenderWindow` (applicable only when `VTK_OPENGL_HAS_EGL` is `ON`, "
"which is the default setting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:56
msgid ""
"`vtkOSOpenGLRenderWindow` (OSMesa, requires that `osmesa.dll` or `libOSMesa."
"so` is installed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:58
msgid ""
"Note: VTK does **not** support OSMesa on macOS, iOS, Android and WebAssembly "
"platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:60
msgid "Multisample anti-aliasing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:62
msgid ""
"Some OpenGL drivers have rendering problems when Multisample anti-aliasing "
"is enabled. It is possible to specify the environment variable "
"`VTK_FORCE_MSAA` to troubleshoot rendering problems with these values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:65
msgid "`0` to disable MSAA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/runtime_settings.md:66
msgid ""
"`1` to enable it regardless even when the driver is known to have problems "
"with MSAA"
msgstr ""
